<#
    Vector-literal spread (0.2): [...a, ...b] splices a's and b's
    elements into a new vector. Vector-literal spread only for this
    version -- variadic parameters and call-site spread are explicitly
    out of scope, see docs/PLAN-0.2.md decision 7 and ROADMAP.md's
    "Language feature ideas under consideration" section.
#>

var a = [1, 2]
var b = [3, 4]

var combined = [...a, ...b]
print combined

var withExtra = [0, ...a, 2.5, ...b, 5]
print withExtra
